name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Petitioner v. Daniel WHITE, Respondent

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Petitioner v. Daniel WHITE, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 16th day of October, 2008, the Petition for Allowance of Appeal is GRANTED on the issue set forth below:
Is the Commonwealth entitled to have lifted a nolle prosequi entered into due to factors beyond the Commonwealth’s control, where the Commonwealth has demonstrated due diligence and speedy trial issues are not implicated?
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

casebody.head_matter:
958 A.2d 1042
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Petitioner v. Daniel WHITE, Respondent.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
Oct. 16, 2008.
